 There's so many people tuning in with us all over the place.

12
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:57,760
 And so we want to just say a special hello.

13
00:00:57,760 --> 00:00:59,880
 If you're tuning in with us online somewhere,

14
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:02,520
 from wherever it is you stream, or if you're listening to this

15
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,240
 at some point in the future, welcome.

16
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:05,440
 We're really glad to have you here.

17
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:09,520
 Special shout out to Portslife, Dayton, Scottsdale, and Boise.

18
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:10,600
 Let's give it up.

19
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:14,080
 Hey, I want to do an exercise with you.

20
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,360
 Now listen, this is going to be a rhetorical exercise.

21
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,980
 I do not need you to speak back to me.

22
00:01:17,980 --> 00:01:21,840
 I need you to think in the quietness of your inner self.

23
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:24,340
 I want you to go through the halls of your personal history

24
00:01:24,340 --> 00:01:26,840
 back to that very first moment where you felt

25
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:32,640
 some sense of personal panic, like some social embarrassment.

26
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,180
 You can work your way back there while I tell you about mine,

27
00:01:35,180 --> 00:01:38,280
 because mine was when I was in the seventh grade

28
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:42,000
 and I joined the football team for the very first time.

29
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:42,800
 I know.

30
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:45,120
 I had not grown up playing football.

31
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:47,880
 I had been around sports, baseball, soccer,

32
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,080
 but I had never really spent any time around football.

33
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:51,080
 I didn't watch it.

34
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,080
 I didn't know the rules.

35
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,360
 I didn't know the position.

36
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:58,040
 And yet what I knew is that I had a bunch of friends

37
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:00,440
 that were all joining the team, and so I was eager to jump

38
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,120
 on board with them as well.

39
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:04,160
 So the day comes, and we make our way out

40
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:08,080
 to try out for a specific position.

41
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,960
 But I didn't know anything about the sport,

42
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,040
 and so I picked the only position that I knew of.

43
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:14,120
 I chose to try out for quarterback.

44
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:17,120
 Did I know any professional quarterbacks?

45
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:17,840
 No.

46
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:20,640
 Did I know how to spin the peel?

47
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,360
 No, I did not.

48
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:25,480
 Did I know that it was the most important position

49
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,580
 on the team?

50
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:27,760
 Of course not.

51
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:31,600
 I just simply knew that this was an important position to--

52
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,680
 this was a position that everybody knew about.

53
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:36,400
 And so the day came for me to try out,

54
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,440
 and what I found out is that the tryout's really

55
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,800
 just a matter of you self-selecting

56
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:40,640
 into what you wanted.

57
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:42,840
 So I got put into this position, and it was amazing.

58
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,720
 I started learning the role really well,

59
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:47,640
 and then eventually, as season started to approach,

60
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:50,520
 we got delegated into a variety of different teams.

61
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:56,360
 Much to my surprise, I was put on the A team, which

62
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:58,960
 was surprising to me because, listen, I was not

63
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,840
 under the illusion that I was God's gift to the sport

64
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,960
 of football.

65
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,960
 I knew that I had worked really hard,

66
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,240
 that I had given it the good college try,

67
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,920
 that I had showed up early and I had stayed late.

68
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,240
 And I thought, man, this is just my coaches recognizing

69
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,680
 the fact that I had really gone for it.

70
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,840
 And so they're rewarding all of my effort.

71
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:18,160
 And so the day comes for us to make our journey

72
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,600
 to my very first football game.

73
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,440
 I grab my gear.

74
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,200
 I board the bus.

75
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:26,400
 I say hey to my buddies, and we go to Paris, Texas.

76
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:28,960
 And in Paris, Texas, we offload from the bus,

77
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,720
 and I do what I always do.

78
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:34,560
 I find my fellow quarterbacks, and I grab a ball,

79
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,560
 and I start to warm up the old arm,

80
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,360
 like eye socket to hip pocket.

81
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,840
 I'm working my drills with these guys

82
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:43,520
 until eventually our coach comes over, and he does what he always

83
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:44,000
 does.

84
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,800
 He does a head count.

85
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:49,320
 And then he does a second head count.

86
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:54,480
 And then he does a third head count.

87
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:57,240
 Because come to find out, he had one more quarterback

88
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,400
 than he was expecting--

89
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,120
 me.

90
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:05,000
 My name had accidentally been placed on the wrong roster.

91
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,800
 And because I was not, in fact, qualified

92
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,400
 to quarterback the best of my 12-year-old companions,

93
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,440
 my coaches decided in that moment

94
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,760
 to remove me from the only position I was familiar with

95
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,640
 and put me in a completely different position

96
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:19,400
 that I had no familiarity with whatsoever.

97
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:22,040
 This is the stuff of prepubescent panic.

98
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:22,920
 OK?

99
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,960
 I was freaking out.

100
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,880
 Like, my whole world had flipped upside down.

101
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:29,240
 It felt like the sky was coming down on top of me

102
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,000
 because I was no longer playing on offense.

103
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,800
 Now I was playing on defense.

104
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,360
 I was no longer calling the shots on the field.

105
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,560
 I was lost on the field.

106
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,840
 I had no idea what I was doing.

107
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:41,520
 I was not under the mistake that I was a part of the A team.

108
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,640
 No, I actually thought that I had made the mistake

109
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,680
 of playing this sport to begin with.

110
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,920
 You see, I had expected one thing,

111
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:54,000
 but I experienced something completely different.

112
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,440
 Now, why do I tell you that?

113
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:59,640
 Because for many of us, faith can feel the same way.

114
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:02,640
 Like you boarded the bus of belief

115
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:05,240
 and you made your way out to the big game

116
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,880
 and then you offloaded and you realized,

117
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,680
 this is nothing like what I thought it was.

118
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:12,720
 Like, I thought not just that I'm lost on the field,

119
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,560
 I'm actually lost in my faith.

120
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,900
 It's not just that I am a part of the wrong roster.

121
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,480
 I might be a part of the wrong religion.

122
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,560
 It's not just that I'm questioning

123
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,640
 how to play this position.

124
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:24,120
 I'm actually questioning all of my claims to belief.

125
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:26,400
 Like, I'm in a position where I'm not sure

126
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,580
 that this is exactly what I thought it was supposed to be.

127
00:05:28,580 --> 00:05:30,000
 I had some expectations,

128
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
 but my experience in walking with God

129
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,160
 has not panned out like I thought it would.

130
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:38,920
 And the result is you've been left with disappointment.

131
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:42,600
 Brene Brown in her book "Rising Strong,"

132
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,560
 she says, "Disappointment is unmet expectations."

133
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:49,320
 And the more significant the expectations,

134
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:52,080
 the more significant the disappointment.

135
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,120
 And listen, there's nothing more significant

136
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,160
 about a person than what they believe about God.

137
00:05:57,160 --> 00:06:00,840
 Which is why today, many young adults,

138
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,800
 some of you included,

139
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,080
 are actually on the road to deconstruction

140
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:05,960
 because your deconstruction from God

141
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,840
 is the result of your disappointment in God.

142
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,040
 Now, here's the thing that we need to know.

143
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,920
 When we wrestle with disappointment on God,

144
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,280
 there's a variety of different reasons

145
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,160
 why that could be happening.

146
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,820
 Like, it could be rooted

147
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:19,560
 in some sort of theological breakdown.

148
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,480
 Like, you thought you believed one thing,

149
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,120
 but then you learned something different,

150
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,680
 and now your spirituality is spiraling.

151
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:29,240
 It could be that you're facing a sociological dilemma.

152
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:32,800
 Like, you know Christians, and you know what they claim,

153
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,120
 but then you know the way they live,

154
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,760
 and all it feels like is hypocrisy,

155
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:38,200
 and all you can do is question the claims they say

156
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,840
 are in fact true.

157
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,400
 Maybe it's not theological, maybe it's not sociological,

158
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:45,160
 maybe it's just circumstantial.

159
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:49,360
 Like, you know God can show up,

160
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,520
 you know He will show up for others,

161
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:53,800
 but it just hasn't happened for you,

162
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:56,840
 and it feels like the circumstances in your life,

163
00:06:56,840 --> 00:07:00,720
 they have gone from good to bad to worse.

164
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:03,560
 And again and again, you found yourself

165
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,520
 facing the unfairness of life,

166
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:08,280
 having your hopes dashed against the rocks of reality.

167
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:11,760
 Whatever the reason, for many people,

168
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,320
 their experience of Christianity

169
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:15,640
 is more synonymous with disappointment

170
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:18,220
 than enjoyment of God.

171
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:24,220
 So, if you're here, and you're somewhere

172
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:28,460
 on the road to deconstruction,

173
00:07:28,460 --> 00:07:30,340
 at the very least wrestling with your belief,

174
00:07:30,340 --> 00:07:32,140
 and at the very most walking away from your belief,

175
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:34,300
 then you need to know this talk is for you.

176
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:38,180
 Because we're gonna see Jesus engage with someone

177
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:43,040
 that is facing their own personal disappointment in God.

178
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,860
 So if you have a Bible, you can grab it,

179
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:47,460
 and you can turn with me to Matthew chapter 11.

180
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:49,380
 We've been in a series called "Deconstructed"

181
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:52,060
 because we know now more than ever before,

182
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:53,500
 people are questioning their faith,

183
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:56,500
 and we don't think that's inherently a bad thing.

184
00:07:56,500 --> 00:08:00,300
 A.J. Swoboda says it in his book, "After Doubt."

185
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:03,660
 "Deconstruction is a double-edged sword.

186
00:08:03,660 --> 00:08:04,820
 "It can edify our faith

187
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:07,640
 "by helping us critically rethink wrong beliefs,

188
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:11,660
 "but it can also go too far and bring our faith to nothing."

189
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:16,580
 You see, there's a major difference in remodeling a room

190
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:18,540
 and tearing a house down.

191
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:22,680
 One is taking a space and making it more livable.

192
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,740
 The other is taking a space

193
00:08:24,740 --> 00:08:27,940
 and rendering it completely inhospitable.

194
00:08:27,940 --> 00:08:29,900
 My goal in this series,

195
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,660
 if you're here for the very first time,

196
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:35,180
 is I want to make the space where your soul resides

197
00:08:35,180 --> 00:08:37,340
 as livable as possible.

198
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:39,460
 Like, I want your faith to flourish.

199
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:42,460
 Like, I want your inner person to thrive.

200
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:43,940
 And yet what we often have to do

201
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,220
 is we have to critically evaluate our belief

202
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:48,540
 and see what parts are weak.

203
00:08:48,540 --> 00:08:50,780
 Like, what in the foundation feels cracked?

204
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:53,540
 What do we actually need to reassess?

205
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:54,420
 And then what does it look like

206
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:56,080
 to not just deconstruct what feels weak,

207
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:59,100
 but actually reconstruct something strong in its place?

208
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:01,540
 That's what we've been doing.

209
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:05,320
 And what we know is that as we step further

210
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,620
 inside the Christian story of reality,

211
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:08,460
 what we often have to do

212
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:12,820
 is deal with the disappointments we feel about that reality,

213
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:14,700
 which is what Jesus is going to do

214
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:17,780
 with a guy by the name of John the Baptist tonight.

215
00:09:17,780 --> 00:09:18,780
 And so we'll pick it up

216
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:21,300
 as they kind of work through a series of steps

217
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:23,580
 on how to deal with disappointment.

218
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:25,780
 So it says this, Matthew chapter 11,

219
00:09:25,780 --> 00:09:27,740
 starting in verse one,

220
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:29,700
 we're just going to take it little by little.

221
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,220
 "When Jesus had finished instructing his 12 disciples,

222
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:36,100
 "he went on from there to teach and preach in their cities.

223
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:39,600
 "Now, when John heard in prison

224
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,120
 "about the deeds of the Christ,

225
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:43,960
 "he sent word by his disciples and said to him,

226
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,020
 "Are you the one who is to come

227
00:09:46,020 --> 00:09:47,720
 "or shall we look for another?"

228
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:51,220
 Now, listen, if you know anything about John B,

229
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:53,660
 not John B from Outer Banks, but John B from the West Bank,

230
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:56,420
 what you need to know is that John the Baptist

231
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:58,020
 is Jesus' guy.

232
00:09:58,020 --> 00:10:01,460
 Like his entire story is one of effectively serving life.

233
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:02,740
 Jesus is hype man.

234
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:03,580
 You know what that is?

235
00:10:03,580 --> 00:10:04,620
 Like it's the guy that comes up

236
00:10:04,620 --> 00:10:06,500
 before the main act takes the stage

237
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:07,780
 and gets the crowd excited

238
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:09,380
 and keeps injecting energy into the room,

239
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:10,780
 make sure the vibes are really great.

240
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:11,980
 Like that's who John is.

241
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:13,380
 He's the forerunner.

242
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:15,180
 Like it says that he's the one

243
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:20,100
 who came to prepare the way for God's Messiah,

244
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:21,740
 the anointed one of Israel.

245
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:24,100
 He baptized Jesus in the Jordan.

246
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,020
 He stood there and he heard the voice from heaven say,

247
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:28,340
 "This is my son with whom I'm well pleased."

248
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:32,520
 He also was self-identified as the voice in the wilderness

249
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,540
 claiming make straight the ways of the Lord.

250
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:37,640
 John was a spiritual giant.

251
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:40,420
 Think about it in your own life.

252
00:10:40,420 --> 00:10:41,860
 Who is the best believer,

253
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:44,700
 like the fiercest of faith that you know?

254
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:47,860
 They don't stand a chance in comparison to John.

255
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:52,180
 John is a spiritual savant,

256
00:10:52,180 --> 00:10:55,020
 literally at the very beginning of his life

257
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,660
 while he's still in his mother's womb.

258
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:59,860
 It says that he received the Holy Spirit.

259
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:02,500
 The best of us does not have that going for him, okay?

260
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,460
 John was just built different.

261
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:07,540
 And yet what we know is despite the fact that his history

262
00:11:07,540 --> 00:11:11,780
 is marked by moments of incredible faithfulness

