00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:05,480
 to change my circumstances?

529
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,560
 Yes!

530
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:09,540
 But that doesn't mean he will.

531
00:23:09,540 --> 00:23:14,040
 He absolutely has the power to change your circumstances.

532
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,880
 He has the power to change John's circumstances,

533
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,040
 yet it does not mean that he will.

534
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:21,020
 It's actually, it's really interesting.

535
00:23:21,020 --> 00:23:22,860
 If you look at the passage we're studying,

536
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:25,240
 the words that Jesus has John's disciples

537
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:30,240
 bring back to him, they're full of messianic prophecy,

538
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:32,680
 all of which Jesus is the fulfillment of.

539
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:38,760
 And yet Jesus conveniently excludes

540
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:43,100
 one element of the prophecy.

